blocks.text: This frame holds an instance of the responsive layout component. Its “layouts” property holds connections to several different frames. As the component's responsive width changes, the component will display its largest layout that fits inside.
Give it a try now by stretching the component’s width.
Note that the component will stretch each layout to fit. If you want to keep your layout’s content centered, wrap its content in a Stack component (as in Desktop and HDDesktop Frames).
Try it out in the preview – and be sure to select “Responsive” in the preview menu.
These layouts are connected to the responsive component. The responsive component will try to show the largest one that will fit.
